&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please Note: We have ONE opening for an Advisory Manager that can be based in one of our many office locations: Charlotte, NC - Atlanta, GA - Boston, MA - Westwood, NY - Wayne, PA - New York, NY - Annapolis, MD - McLean, VA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why work at Modera Wealth?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Modera Wealth Management is an independent, fee-only firm that strives to make a lasting positive impact on the lives of our clients through comprehensive financial planning and intelligent investment management. Modera is fast-growing and has a track record of providing career development opportunities from entry level to ownership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since 1983, Modera has been committed to being an advisor firm, and not a firm of advisors. Our growth has been driven by a desire to give clients a personalized service experience with our distinct combination of professional excellence and a friendly, relatable work style. Through this vision, we have grown to more than 200 employees in 19 offices along the East Coast, managing more than $15B in assets for more than 6,000 individuals, families, and businesses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an &lt;strong&gt;Advisory Manager&lt;/strong&gt; that will be responsible for leading a team of financial planning associates to deliver high-quality support to our advisors. This role balances direct client service with team management, including performance monitoring, and ensuring adherence to firm compliance and planning standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate the work of Planning Associates to ensure efficient distribution of financial planning deliverables to advisors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor the quality and accuracy of planning work; enforce best practices, templates, and review protocols established by the Planning Associate Team Lead&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide hands-on mentorship, coaching, and ongoing feedback to Planning Associates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Address day-to-day personnel needs, including scheduling, workload balancing, and performance-related concerns with the support of the Planning Associate Team Leader&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in communicating departmental goals and expectations, guide team members in their execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct regular one-on-one meetings with direct reports to provide coaching, support professional growth, and ensure alignment of goals, responsibilities, and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor progress toward team and individual SMART goals, offering course correction and support as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct annual performance reviews and contribute to ongoing evaluation of team members’ development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with HR and Planning Associate Team Leader to support career development and make recommendations for promotions within the planning team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current on financial planning tools, technologies, and methodology to ensure planners are equipped with the resources they need&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support team culture, morale, and cross-office collaboration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Occasional travel may be required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What are we looking for?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want a team player who can leverage the strength of the firm to deliver outstanding results and solutions. We are looking for people who embody Modera’s core values:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confident Humility – a quintessential team player, willing to do whatever it takes to get the job done, with pragmatic optimism&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contagious Growth Mindset – a continuous learner with intellectual curiosity who strives for excellence and inspires others&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;T

